<item>
            <title>[LU-12974] Running lfsck with dry-run (-n) should not move orphan obhect to lost+found</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12974</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;For the OST orphan issue we had reported  we had a chance to run lfsck at the maintenance window last month. We ran lfsck with dry-run &quot;-r -n -o&quot;, but actually (unexpectedly) it moved orphans to lost+found. It should not fix orphans as it is dry-run. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
